\noindent\underline{\textbf{Final Project}}:

\noindent
Your final project will be to construct a creative work. This could be (but is not limited to) an infographic, a comic book, a sculpture, or a short film. A rubric for this project will be posted mid-semester, but roughly it should:
\begin{itemize}
  \item Summarize a significant portion of course content knowledge and present it in a clear, concise, and creative manner.
  \item Draw connections between different concepts in the course, and quickly describe the links \textit{for reference}. This is not a document you would use to \textit{teach} the content, but is something that \textit{demonstrates your knowledge and expertise in the content to your classmates and instructor}.
  \item This will be due on the last day of class (Friday, May 2nd).
  \item There will be a list of \textit{minimum requirements}. If you \textit{significantly exceed} the requirements (demonstrating substantial effort and expertise), this assignment may be eligible to count for a larger percentage of your final course grade.
\end{itemize}


