\noindent\underline{\textbf{Optional Comprehensive Final Exam}}:

\noindent
This will take place Monday, May. 5th during your scheduled class time (so it will be the same length as previous exams, but have questions from the entire semester).
After taking it, you can decide if it should be graded.
If you choose to have your final exam graded, it \textit{will} replace your lowest test score, for better or worse. If you are happy with your grade on the first three exams, you do not need to take the comprehensive final. However, if you had one or two bad exams, you could \textit{significantly} raise your grade due to the adaptive grading scheme.

